#: ../../../getting_started/index.md:1
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr "開始使用"

#: ../../../getting_started/index.md:3
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "介紹"

#: ../../../getting_started/index.md:5
msgid ""
"Welcome to VTK! We recommend that you start by reading [The VTK Book]"
"(https://book.vtk.org), a comprehensive guide to VTK that covers all aspects "
"of its functionality. Additionally, you may find it helpful to explore the "
"[VTK Examples](https://examples.vtk.org), a collection of useful reference "
"materials that demonstrate how to use VTK's different modules and features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/index.md:11
msgid ""
"Before diving into VTK's functionality, ensure that your system meets its "
"[system requirements](#system-requirements). Depending on your programming "
"experience and needs, you can choose different programming languages to work "
"with VTK. We have documentation on how to use VTK with [Python](#using-"
"python), [Jupyter](#using-jupyter), [C++ and CMake](#using-c-and-cmake), "
"[Javascript](#using-javascript), and [WebAssembly](#using-webassembly)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/index.md:18
msgid ""
"Lastly, to help address your specific needs, you may also consider exploring "
"existing free and open-source [frameworks or applications](#using-existing-"
"frameworks-and-applications) that already leverage VTK. These frameworks and "
"applications can be extended and customized to work for specific use cases "
"and may provide ready-to-use solutions for your project."
msgstr ""

