#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:37
msgid "**Building an executable**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:39
msgid ""
"Once VTK is installed using either of the methods above you can use it in "
"your project utilizing the [find_package](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/"
"latest/command/find_package.html) infrastructure of cmake:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:44
msgid ""
"find_package(VTK\n"
"  COMPONENTS\n"
"  .. list of vtk modules to link to\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"# your executable\n"
"add_executable(testExample ...)\n"
"\n"
"# link to required VTK libraries\n"
"target_link_libraries(testExample\n"
"  PRIVATE\n"
"   ${VTK_LIBRARIES}\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"vtk_module_autoinit(\n"
"  TARGETS testExample\n"
"  MODULES ${VTK_LIBRARIES}\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:65
msgid ""
"{cmake:command}`vtk_module_autoinit` is responsible for triggering static "
"code construction required for some VTK classes. For more details regarding "
"the autoinit system of VTK see [here](../api/cmake/ModuleSystem.md#autoinit)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:68
msgid ""
"The list of required vtk modules depends on the files `#include`d in your "
"code. The module a header file belongs to is determined in most cases by its "
"location in the VTK source tree. For, example `vtkXMLPolyDataReader` is "
"located under `IO/XML` so it belongs to the `IOXML` module, to verify check "
"the accompanying [`vtk.module`](https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/blob/"
"master/IO/XML/vtk.module) file in the same directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:72
msgid ""
"The above method works in most cases but it does not express the "
"dependencies that some module have. A better (and easier) way to find the "
"required modules is the [VTKModulesForCxx](https://examples.vtk.org/site/"
"Python/Utilities/VTKModulesForCxx) script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:75
msgid ""
"For example, running the script on the [CylinderExample](https://examples."
"vtk.org/site/Cxx/GeometricObjects/CylinderExample) we get the following "
"suggestion:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:78
msgid ""
"find_package(VTK\n"
" COMPONENTS\n"
"    CommonColor\n"
"    CommonCore\n"
"    FiltersSources\n"
"    RenderingCore\n"
"    #\n"
"    # These modules are suggested since they implement an existing module.\n"
"    # You may need to uncomment one or more of these.\n"
"    # If vtkRenderWindow is used and you want to use OpenGL,\n"
"    #   you also need the RenderingOpenGL2 module.\n"
"    # If vtkRenderWindowInteractor is used,\n"
"    #    uncomment RenderingUI and possibly InteractionStyle.\n"
"    # If text rendering is used, uncomment RenderingFreeType\n"
"    #\n"
"    # InteractionStyle  # implements VTK::RenderingCore\n"
"    # RenderingCellGrid # implements VTK::RenderingCore\n"
"    # RenderingFreeType # implements VTK::RenderingCore\n"
"    # RenderingOpenGL2  # implements VTK::RenderingCore\n"
"    # RenderingUI       # implements VTK::RenderingCore\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:102
msgid ""
"Based on the suggestions of the script and the template above the relevant "
"sections of the `CMakeLists.txt` are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:104
msgid ""
"...\n"
"find_package(VTK COMPONENTS\n"
"  CommonColor\n"
"  CommonCore\n"
"  FiltersSources\n"
"  InteractionStyle\n"
"  RenderingContextOpenGL2\n"
"  RenderingCore\n"
"  RenderingFreeType\n"
"  RenderingGL2PSOpenGL2\n"
"  RenderingOpenGL2\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"add_executable(CylinderExample CylinderExample.cxx)\n"
"target_link_libraries(CylinderExample PRIVATE ${VTK_LIBRARIES})\n"
"# vtk_module_autoinit is needed\n"
"vtk_module_autoinit(\n"
"  TARGETS CylinderExample\n"
"  MODULES ${VTK_LIBRARIES}\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started/using_cpp.md:127
msgid ""
"The full source of the example can be found [here](https://examples.vtk.org/"
"site/Cxx/GeometricObjects/CylinderExample/)."
msgstr ""

